OL,7,FHe went on to admit his actions saying
OL,8,Fhe was motivated by an anti-government
OL,9,Fideology but denied intending to kill
OL,10,Fa police officer.
OL,12,FDuring a hearing at the Old Bailey,
OL,13,FDighton declined the opportunity to be
OL,14,Flegally represented despite being told
OL,15,Fthe maximum sentence for some of the
OL,16,Fcharges was life in prison.
