OL,7,FHe told Mrs Justice Cheema-Grubb:
OL,8,F"Authority is not my problem. It's the
OL,9,Fuse of authority which to me is the
OL,10,Fproblem, the use of authority I have
OL,11,Fseen since I was 15, that's my
OL,12,Fproblem."
OL,14,FThe senior judge asked him again if he
OL,15,Fwould like to delay the case so he
OL,16,Fcould take legal advice.
OL,18,FThe defendant replied: "That will be
OL,19,Fall right, thank you. I perfectly
OL,20,Funderstand it."
