OL,7,FThe court was told he had no previous
OL,8,Fconvictions and there was a question
OL,9,Fwhether he had Asperger syndrome or an
OL,10,Fautism spectrum disorder.
OL,12,FDighton was remanded into custody to
OL,13,Fbe sentenced on 13 May at the Central
OL,14,FCriminal Court.
OL,16,FAsked if he understood, the softly
OL,17,Fspoken, bearded defendant told the
OL,18,Fjudge: "It seems perfectly salient."
